author: maxb
msg: SWIG cleanup: The apr_file_t ** typemaps were identical to the general
OUTPARAM ones! Kill redundancy! Redundancy must die!
[in subversion/bindings/swig/]
* include/svn_types.swg: Add 'apr_file_t **' to the OUTPARAM list.
* include/apr.swg: Delete the 'apr_file_t **' typemaps.

author: maxb
msg: Generalize the hack that NULL-initializes commit_info parameters to cover
all languages, not just Perl, and the new svn_commit_info_t type, not just
svn_client_commit_info_t.
This fixes Ruby test SvnClientTest::test_commit, which broke when I removed
blanket NULL-initialization from the Ruby typemaps in r20383.
* svn_client.i: Remove old version. Add FIXME to nearby piece of code that
probably needs svn_client_commit_info_t -> svn_commit_info_t
generalization as well.
* include/svn_types.swg: Add new version.

author: maxb
msg: * subversion/bindings/swig/include/svn_swigcompat.swg: Add a pre-1.3.28
replacement for %append_output(obj), a macro which I will soon be
introducing much use of.
